snippet.textDisplay: Thanks, very interesting. Can you estimate what percentage of positives are asymptomatic and will remain so? Also what percentage of asymptomatics are communicable? Is it true that if false positives are more frequent than the prevalence in the general population then false positives are more likely than true ones?
